article.headline: TCU 70, Texas-Pan American 58
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Ronnie Moss and Zvonko Buljan each recorded a double-double as TCU defeated Texas-Pan American 70-58 Wednesday night. Moss finished with 15 points and 11 assists and Buljan added 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Horned Frogs (10-9). Aaron Urbanus and Nick Weiermiller each scored 13 points to lead the Broncs (3-17). TCU dominated inside, scoring 36 points in the paint and outrebounding Texas-Pan American 37-26. The Horned Frogs also had 15 second-chance points and shot 57.4 percent while limiting the Broncs to 37 percent. TCU was up 36-27 at halftime, scored the first five points of the second half and led by double digits the rest of the way. After six lead changes over the game's first nine minutes, the Horned Frogs took the lead for good with 10-0 run which put them ahead 23-14.
